sentences: After his graduation in 1959, Hoeffler moved to New York, where he worked as a master printer in a studio while building his career as a photographer.
He moved to Toronto, Canada in 1971, where he carried on with his passion for photographing musicians, festivals and clubs.
Many of Hoeffler's photographs feature in  the 2000 Emmy Awards-nominated documentary by Ken Burns, "Jazz".
Paul Hoeffler died of cancer in 2005.
Paul Hoeffler retrieves al lost world" City Newspaper, 8 January 2003

Hoeffler is mostly known for his photographs of the American Jazz scene of the 1950s and 1960s and of Jazz icons such as Louis Armstrong, Duke Ellington, Nat King Cole, Oscar Peterson, Jimmy Smith,  Count Basie, Sarah Vaughan and Billie Holiday.
